Abia State Governor, Okezie Ikpeazu has revealed how farmers/herders conflict are resolved in the state.  Appearing on a Channels Television programme, the Abia state Governor who revealed that there is a Farmers-Herders Resolution Committee in the state which is headed by the Commissioner of Police, also said that they pay a compensation of N100,000 for any cow that is killed on account of a misunderstanding between the farmers and the herders and pay the same amount for farmlands destroyed by strayed cows. The Governor who noted that there’s been a spike in the abduction, rape and killing of farmers in the state, added that sometimes those behind the act don’t have cows. He described those behind the act as infiltrators who disguise as herdsmen and also averred that they will be going after such people. Watch the video below.; A post shared by Lindaikejiblog (@lindaikejiblogofficial) ABUJA (Sundiata Post) - President Muhamadu Buhari's plan to set up cattle colonies accross Nigeria for Fulani herdsmen and their cows suffered it first setback on Friday with the rejection of the proposal by Abia State Governor, Dr. Okezie Ikpeazu. In a statement signed by his Chief Press Secretary, Mr… In "Local News" Aba    -      Gov. Okezie Ikpeazu of Abia has said that all the roads constructed by his administration are products of careful and thorough research. Ikpeazu made this known in Aba while briefing journalists on his activities in the state. The governor, who spoke on the four-point programme… In "News" UMUAHIA (Sundiata Post) - Abia State Governor, Dr Okezie Ikpeazu, has congratulated students and teachers in the state over the ranking of the state as the number one state in the May/June 2015 West African School Certificate Examination (WASSCE) result as released by the West African Examination Council. A statement… In "News"